   {:e #blake3 "aac89d2216bd7263c2ec2975fa57ae58768927797d3aaecf0a1ac6760fb90422" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: crystallize_concepts() exists in the kernel with 3 tests but is NEVER called from the CLI. Uncategorized observations (those not matching any concept) accumulate forever without forming new concepts. This blocks the developmental trajectory: without emergent concepts, the system is stuck at the sensorimotor stage with only 5 innate schemas. APPROACH: In harvest.rs, after collecting harvest candidates: (1) Query all observations with :exploration/embedding but WITHOUT :exploration/concept. These are the uncategorized set. (2) For each, load the embedding (bytes_to_embedding) and body text (:exploration/body). (3) Call crystallize_concepts(observations, JOIN_THRESHOLD, MIN_CLUSTER_SIZE). MIN_CLUSTER_SIZE=3 means at least 3 similar uncategorized observations are needed. (4) For each NewConcept returned: (a) Call concept_to_datoms(concept, timestamp) to generate the concept entity datoms. (b) Call membership_datoms(concept.entity, &concept.members) to link members. (c) Write all datoms to the store in the harvest transaction. (5) Report crystallization: 'crystallized 2 new concepts: event-processing (5 members), error-handling (3 members)'. (6) The next observe call will now find these emergent concepts via find_nearest_concept and assign new observations to them. ACCEPTANCE: (A) After 10 diverse observations (3 about events, 3 about errors, 4 unrelated), harvest crystallizes at least 1 concept (with hash embedder, requires keyword overlap). (B) After crystallization, braid status shows emergent concepts with member_count > 0. (C) After crystallization, a new observation about 'events' matches the emergent event concept (not just innate schemas). (D) braid harvest output includes crystallization count. (E) crystallize_concepts is called with the correct embedder (same as observe uses). CONSIDERATIONS: Crystallization is computationally O(n^3) in the uncategorized count. With typical n < 50, this is < 125K operations per harvest. If n grows large (> 200), consider pre-filtering by timestamp (only recent observations). The MIN_CLUSTER_SIZE=3 threshold prevents noise — isolated observations don't form concepts until corroborated. DEPENDS-ON: LIFECYCLE-OBSERVE (concepts must update before harvest can meaningfully crystallize). FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/harvest.rs" :op :assert}
